but this 500-ton globetrotting &quot;worm&quot; really gets around by using every mode of transportation that can carry its bulk, including several modes funded, serviced or built by the Minnesota Department of Transportation (Mn/DOT). <br>
<br>
Once the machine arrives at a Fort Snelling field near the airport, crews will reassemble it, a task that's expected to take several weeks. Sometime around Halloween, the machine can begin its 16-month job of eating underground rocks to tunnel and simultaneously pave a section of the future LRT line being built by Mn/DOT. <br>
<br>
